<task id="WCWE-013" project="UI Create Wizard Enhancements R1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Fix duplicate title bars in SummarizeFiles wizard and Assign Work step</title>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <tags>frontend, shared-library, wizard</tags>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    E-11: The SummarizeFiles wizard and Assign Work follow-on step render with their own
    title bar when opened as Dataverse dialogs, creating a duplicate title bar (Dataverse
    dialog chrome already provides one). Fix by setting hideTitle={true} on WizardShell
    in both cases.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior frontend developer with expertise in Fluent UI v9, React, and shared component libraries</role>

  <goal>No duplicate title bar appears in any wizard dialog opened via Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo.</goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-006">Code Pages are standalone dialogs opened via navigateTo. They inherit the Dataverse dialog chrome which includes its own title bar.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-006.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SummarizeFilesWizard/</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/CreateWorkAssignment/</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WizardShell/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      When Code Page wizards are opened as Dataverse dialogs via Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo
      with target: 2, the Dataverse platform renders its own dialog title bar. If the
      WizardShell component also renders its title bar, users see two title bars stacked.
      The SummarizeFiles wizard and the Assign Work follow-on step both exhibit this issue.
      The fix is straightforward: pass hideTitle={true} to WizardShell so only the
      platform-provided title bar appears.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      No task dependencies. This is a standalone fix that can run in parallel with other
      Phase 2 tasks.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="identify-occurrences">Search for WizardShell usage in SummarizeFilesWizard and CreateWorkAssignment components to locate where hideTitle should be set.</step>
    <step order="2" name="fix-summarize">Add hideTitle={true} to WizardShell in SummarizeFilesWizard component.</step>
    <step order="3" name="fix-assign-work">Add hideTitle={true} to WizardShell in the Assign Work follow-on step component.</step>
    <step order="4" name="verify-other-wizards">Audit all other wizard components to confirm no other instances have duplicate title bars.</step>
    <step order="5" name="build-verify">Run npm build in the shared library to verify compilation.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SummarizeFilesWizard/ (modified — hideTitle prop)</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/CreateWorkAssignment/ (modified — hideTitle prop)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">SummarizeFiles wizard shows only the Dataverse dialog title bar — no duplicate</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Assign Work follow-on step shows only the Dataverse dialog title bar — no duplicate</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No other wizard dialogs exhibit duplicate title bars</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Shared library builds without errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
